        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 6:56PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 655 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Spruce Pine, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spruce Pine, Marion, Lake James, B.R. Parkway-Little Switzerland To
Linville, B.R. Parkway-Craggy To Little Switzerland, Nebo, North
Cove, Celo, Ashford, and Little Switzerland.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
